SOUTH Africa's women's wheelchair tennis star, Kgothatso ‘KG’ Montjane, and the country’s leading quad ace Lucas Sithole, will jet off to the United States this Sunday to take part in two important International Tennis Federation (ITF) tournaments.The first stop for the two aces will be in Rome at the Georgia Open, the tournament which will serve as a preparatory event ahead of the higher-level Cajun Classic tournament to be staged in Baton Rouge.The world’s best wheelchair tennis players are due to line-up for the forthcoming top-flight tournaments, with the first event being an ITF level 1 and the second, an ITF Super Series tournament. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsu_a6rdtL730InpVdyB5gU9y53XFXin--7ncCdYU8HRcoWCgchAlpCsnscolXJOfpVw8UJ2NgmeZ8McAraz2GNsTV8zh0KCN8s-ZBbnxQA884mtcCa8mJ0Zpe50zQAiYjCpm3F28-fh_8t74lMWI-kTgdAQsgTgOFana70YVuASpijOPoMsDg7KdLtGr0HTi5fSIy7Hy5KfO6D9XtQaGo0BWs8nmdl2VmZ7fT4w7h2LHK9O-tWGgWy7sAIVEO7Xh5ibzoiVlbNBfLptoO0i\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzF1J88PJEzGgEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
